Frink! is a Reddit client designed for the Blackbery Playbook.  It is Open Source and Commercial.  

Frink! is licensed under a Creative Commons Attribution-NonCommercial-ShareAlike 3.0 Unported License.  All of the source is freely available, assuming you are using it for a non-commercial application, and share your code.  For commercial licensing or any other uses, please contact me at http://jbeckwith.com.

Frink! is written in as3 and mxml, using Adobe Flex 4.5.  The project files for Flash Builder 4.5 are included, along with any necessary libraries. 

For more information, please visit Frink! at http://frinkapp.com.

Version 1.1.0 includes:
* mail - you can now send and receive mail
* gesture support - swipe to move panels around instead of hitting the arrows
* comments now render in html


